<Title>Good technology for the casual user 
<Date>Fri Oct 05 00:00:00 CST 2007
<Content>I found the audio/video quality and storage capacity of the 3rd generation iPod nano to cover my basic portable entertainment needs. As a frequent air traveller, I find that the nano's video capability in a slim form factor makes a few hours on a plane go by much more quickly without having to lug the extra weight of a laptop or portable dvd player.  Extremely easy to configure, update, and charge.  Downside:  I had the iPod touchpad and screen become completely unresponsive several times in the past few months (it wasn't the battery running out) and had to reset (per instructions from Apple's website) it by holding down the center button and menu function simultaneously until the logo appeared and the screen restarted. This was alarming the first time it happened since I didn't know how to reset the iPod -- but I didn't lose any stored data; so it's a minor concern to me now that I know how to remedy it.   
